nodes.bodyText:
I think this changes the behavior that was there before. Before your changes I see:
if (useMap) {
            if (readOnly) {
                startGeoButton.setText(R.string.geopoint_view_read_only);

which implies that if the question is read-only, the map should open and show the point but not allow it to be changed. Can you verify what the prior behavior was with a readonly geopoint with map and a default value, make sure it's still the same, and that there's a test for it?
This is the case I was referring to at https://github.com/getodk/collect/pull/3877/files#r449199637.

